description:
# Looping with Conditions

Sometimes you don't know HOW MANY times to loop - you just know WHEN to stop. That's where **while loops** come in!

## While Loop Basics

A while loop repeats as long as a condition is true:

```csharp
int health = 100;
int damage = 15;

while (health > 0)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"Health: {health}");
    health -= damage;
}
Console.WriteLine("Defeated!");
```

**Important:** Make sure your condition eventually becomes false, or you'll have an infinite loop!

## While vs For

**Use for loop when:** You know how many iterations you need
```csharp
for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++)  // Exactly 10 times
```

**Use while loop when:** You loop until a condition changes
```csharp
while (playerHealth > 0)  // Until player dies
```

## Common Patterns

```csharp
// Countdown until threshold
int gold = 100;
while (gold >= 20)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"Buying item for 20 gold. Gold: {gold}");
    gold -= 20;
}

// Level up until max
int level = 1;
while (level < 10)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"Level {level}");
    level++;
}
```

## Your Quest

1. **Healing Simulation**: Start with 50 health, heal 10 each turn until health >= 100
2. **Resource Gathering**: Gather gold (start at 0, gain 45 each round) until gold >= 200
3. **Enemy Waves**: Fight 5 waves of enemies, display wave number
4. **Level Grind**: Start at level 1, gain 1 level each iteration until level 15

